"### Pubertal status reported by the parent
The pubertal report is only available separately for boys and girls. Here we calculate a single variable from either the one or the other.
```
var promises = use(["pubertdev_ss_male_category_p", "pubertdev_ss_female_category_p"]);
```
This function is called for each participant and returns the values that is there. If both values are not defined the returned value is empty.
```
function calcPubStatus(a, b) {
      if (isNaN(a) && isNaN(b))
         return '';
      if (isNaN(a))
         return b;
      return a;
}
```

The next section will call the above defined function for each session. Use it as a template in your own scores.
```
Promise.all(promises).then( function() {
  var data = new DataFrame(allMeasures);
  data = data.map(row => row.set('parent_pubertal_status', +calcPubStatus(row.get("pubertdev_ss_male_category_p"), row.get("pubertdev_ss_female_category_p"))));
  update(data, 'parent_pubertal_status');
});
```
